This paper discusses the SCION network architecture, which is primarily focused on improving the scalability, control, and security of inter-domain networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the attacker model and limitations of SCION, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses research highlights, which could fall under several categories, including cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
